The paper introduces a new approach to representing argumentation frameworks using matrices, which has advantages in terms of computability. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories within computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and game theory (cs.GT).
